
VISA REQUIREMENTS FOR GREEK CITIZENS
Visa requirements for Greek citizens are administrative entry restrictions by the authorities of other states placed on citizens of Greece. As of May 2018, Greek citizens had visa-free or visa on arrival access to 185 countries and territories, ranking the Greek passport 6th in terms of travel freedom (tied with Australian and Belgian passports) according to the Henley Passport Index.
